Title: THE LAST KEY
Credit: Written by
Author: Valerio Narcisi
Draft date: 2026-04-15
Contact: test@ohwriters.dev

====

FADE IN:

EXT. OLD HOUSE - DUSK

A narrow stone house sits at the end of a gravel lane. Ivy climbs one wall. A FOR SALE sign leans crookedly in the overgrown grass.

ELENA, 40s, stands at the front door holding a single iron key. She has not been here in twenty years.

She slides the key into the lock. It turns.

INT. OLD HOUSE - FOYER - CONTINUOUS

Dust sheets cover everything. Elena steps inside. The door creaks shut behind her.

ELENA
(quietly)
Hello?

No answer.

She walks deeper into the house, running her fingers along a dust sheet. It comes away grey.

INT. OLD HOUSE - KITCHEN - MOMENTS LATER

A yellowed note is taped to the refrigerator. Elena pulls it off. Her mother's handwriting.

ELENA (V.O.)
If you are reading this, I am gone, and so is your father, and so is the dog. The key works on one more lock. You will find it.

She folds the note carefully and puts it in her pocket.

INT. OLD HOUSE - STAIRCASE - NIGHT

Elena climbs. Each step groans. At the top of the stairs she pauses, looking down the hallway.

Three doors. Her old bedroom. Her parents' bedroom. A third door she doesn't recognise.

She walks toward the third door.

INT. OLD HOUSE - HIDDEN ROOM - CONTINUOUS

The room is small, windowless. A single wooden chest sits in the centre of the floor.

Elena kneels before it. The key fits.

Inside: photographs. Hundreds of them. Elena at seven, at twelve, at twenty. Her parents at every age. The dog.

She lifts one photo. Her own wedding, from a day she no longer speaks about.

ELENA
(to herself)
You kept all of it.

She sits on the floor surrounded by the photographs, and begins, slowly, to smile.

SMASH CUT TO:

EXT. OLD HOUSE - DAWN

The FOR SALE sign is still there, still crooked. But the house is awake now: lights on in every window.

ELENA (V.O.)
I didn't sell it.

FADE OUT.

THE END.
